               <head>Commentary on Rumi's Masnavi</head>
               <msContents class="http://id.loc.gov/authorities/subjects/sh2008109079 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85129649">
                  <summary>1 copy of Mas̱navī-i maʻnavī</summary>
                  <msItem n="1" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1055-item1">
                     <textLang mainLang="fa">Persian</textLang>
                     <note>
                        <p>A commentary on the first daftar of 
                <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="ark:/81055/vdc_100166176928.0x000001 viaf_98930150" role="aut">Rūmī</persName>'s 
                <title key="work_20506">Mas̱navī-i maʻnavī</title>by an unnamed author who cites commentaries by Najafī (possibly Muḥammad Hāshim ibn Muḥammad Kāẓim al-Ḥasanī al-Ḥusaynī al-Najafī, see Delhi Persian 1044B) and Nūr Allāh‏ [Aḥrārī (fl. 1622-3)].
                        </p>
                        <p>Copy defective at end; nastaʻlīq; rubrications; worm-eaten.</p>
                        <p>Early 19th century.</p>
                     </note>
                     <note/>
                     <author>
